[5] Cholera - India (Gujarat State)
Date: Thu 14 Aug 2014
Source: Times of India, Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/vadodara/Parts-of-Godhra-declared-cholera-hit-youth-hospitalized/articleshow/40254822.cms


Parts of Godhra [Panchmahal district, Gujarat state] have been declared cholera affected after a case surfaced in the town. Areas surrounding the town have been declared as cholera threatened in the wake of the case. A youth from Signal Falia, admitted at civil hospital with symptoms of cholera, was tested positive for the disease.

Godhra sub-divisional magistrate NF Vasava who has been designated as the cholera control officer said that the areas falling within a radius of 3 km of Signal Falia have been declared as cholera affected. While the case is the only one to be reported in the town, the declaration is mandatory under the Cholera Control Act.

Areas falling within an 8 km radius of the Godhra town have also been declared as cholera threatened. The administration has started distributing chlorine tablets to the residents besides starting super chlorination of water being supplied in the town. Vasava said that necessary precautions were being taken in the town.

