[7] Shigellosis - Jordan (Karak Governorate)
Date: Wed 13 Aug 2014
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/shigella-outbreak-sickens-scores-in-karak-jordan-40348/


At least 150 cases of foodborne illness has been reported in the Shihabieh area in Karak, Jordan, according to a Jordan Times report Mon 11 Aug 2014. An unspecified number of patients who presented with symptoms required hospitalization. Laboratory analysis on the stool samples of the patients and from a local restaurant that serves hummus revealed the presence of Shigella.

"The ministry's health team took precautions by closing the suspected restaurant until the results of the samples taken from there are fully tested," head of the ministry's communicable diseases department, Bashir Qasir told reporters.

[Byline: Robert Herriman]

